The paper focuses on exploring performance and energy trade-offs in heterogeneous multicore architectures, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the use of simulation frameworks for power estimation, which could fall under the category of performance evaluation (cs.PF). The paper also discusses the impact of workload nature on performance/energy trade-off, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for dynamically reconfigurable HSAs, which could fall under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET).
